A serving member of the Oyo State House of Assembly, Ademola Olusegun Popoola, is dead.Daily Post reports that Popoola died in the early hours of Wednesday at the University College Hospital (UCH) Ibadan after suffering from a kidney-related disease. The lawmaker was elected in 2019 under the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP)Â  to serve the people of Ibadan South-East Constituency II at the Oyo State House of Assembly.He died at the age of 46.Until his death, Popoola was the Chairman, House Committee on Local Government and Chieftaincy Matters.Oyekunle Oyetunji, Media Adviser to the Speaker of the state House of Assembly, Adebo Ogundoyin, confirmed the death of the lawmaker on Wednesday.